Sentencas: Anode supported cells were thermal cycled in the temperature range 200-750 degrees C under various conditions: (1) without hydrogen supply, (2) with hydrogen supply, and (3) applying negative current (without hydrogen).
Titulo: Thermal cycling of anode supported solid oxide fuel cells under various conditions: Electrical anode protection

Sentencas: Power density and impedance spectra were measured after several cycles and cycling durability was compared for each condition.
Titulo: Thermal cycling of anode supported solid oxide fuel cells under various conditions: Electrical anode protection

Sentencas: Post-material analyses were conducted on the anode layers of the thermal cycled cells, using scanning electron microscopy, energy dispersive spectroscopy, and Brunauer-Emmett-Teller.
Titulo: Thermal cycling of anode supported solid oxide fuel cells under various conditions: Electrical anode protection

Sentencas: There were no appreciable changes in performance and anode microstructure after the cycling test in the case of 'Condition 2 and 3'; however, the cell was significantly degraded after a few cycles under 'Condition 1 (the slow rate)', due to re-oxidation of Ni anode.
Titulo: Thermal cycling of anode supported solid oxide fuel cells under various conditions: Electrical anode protection

Sentencas: The results indicate that the electrical method (applying a negative current) has an effect for anode protection equivalent to that of the conventional chemical method (cover gas supply).
Titulo: Thermal cycling of anode supported solid oxide fuel cells under various conditions: Electrical anode protection

Sentencas: This electrical method is preferred, particularly in consideration of emergency shutdown events with fuel loss and fuel economy penalty.
Titulo: Thermal cycling of anode supported solid oxide fuel cells under various conditions: Electrical anode protection
